commit.message:
Default to current dir if there is no $HOME env var

On AWS Lambda, and potentially other platforms, there is no $HOME. In
those cases, calling Path(None) throws an error. With this change,
it'll call Path("") instead, which is equivalent to Path(".").

commit.message:
Add unformatted_columns and formula_columns to sheet_to_df (#40)

* Fix and update pre-commit-hooks

* Add unformatted_columns and formula_columns to sheet_to_df

This will enable users to pull certain columns with the
ValueRenderOption set to either FORMULA or UNFORMATTED_VALUES for
specific columns.

* Add values_get_batch function to gspread Spreadsheets

This is necessary to make as few extra calls as possible. It's
currently not implemented in `gspread` so I'm adding this for
now. Hopefully once https://github.com/burnash/gspread/pull/705 gets
merged I can remove this.

* Rename values_get_batch to values_batch_get

This matches the proposed PR to gspread and more closely aligns with
the Google API name.

* Move spread.py tests into spread_test.py

* Allow unformatted_columns and formula_columns to take list of names

This makes these a bit more flexible. If the columns passed in are all
numbers, they will be treated as indeces, otherwise,
we will find the indeces.

* Fix how values are pulled and cleaned

* Add test for formula_columns and raw_columns
